
                                        Angular - Front End Techonolgy

                                                Basic Commands


                                 1. to create a project - ng new project-name / ng new project-name --routing

                                 2. to run Angular project - ng serve / ng serve --open

                                 3. to generate component - ng g component-name

                                 4. to generate service - ng g s service-name


                                            Basic Building blocks

                                         ............................   


                                  1. Module - Toimport third party library

                                  2. Component-to create a new html,css,ts file (root component-app component)    

                                  3. Data Binding - share data inside component

                                      3.1 One way Binding - data sharing only in one direction
                                      
                                          3.1.1 Componenet (ts) to view (html)

                                          3.1.1.1 String Interpulation -{{expression}}

                                          3.1.1.2 property Binding -[atribute name]='property name'

                                      3.1.2 View (html) component (ts)

                                          3.1.2.1 Event Binding (event name)="function-name()"

                                          3.1.2.2 Event Binding using $event (event name)="function-name($event)"

                                          3.1.2.3 Event Binding using template referencing variable - #variable-name

                                      3.2 two way Binding - data sharing only in both direction

                                         3.2.1 ngModle - import formsModule in AppModule
                                         -[(ngModle)]="property-name" , property-name should defined in ts file

                                  4. Angular routimg - to set path for component in appRoutingModule 
                                      - {path:value,component:class-name}
                                      -  use router-outlet selector inside the root component

                                  5. Dependency Injection - to share data between dependent classes

                                  6. Angular services - to hold redundent       
                                 
                                  7. ngSubmit

                                  8. Angular Directives - To manupulate DOM

                                     8.1 Component Directives

                                     8.2 Structural Directives

                                      8.2.1 - *ngFor
                                      8.2.2 - *ngIf

                                     8.3 Atribute Directives

                                     
                                  9. Angular Forms 

                                     9.1 Template Driven Forms - first design html

                                     9.2 Model Driven Forms - first design in ts file

                                       9.2.1 Reactive forms - form group , form array , form control
                                               - Add validations
                                               - Import ReactiveformsModule


                                  10. Local Storage

                                     10.1 setItem

                                     10.2 getItem

                                     10.3 removeItem

                                  11. Parent Child Communication

                                     11.1. Parent to child - @Input

                                  12. Angular Pipe

                                  13. Front end - back end

                                     13.1 Import HTTPClientModule

                                     13.2 Inject HttpClient 

                                     13.3 Using HttpClient make Api calls

                                  14. Asynchronus call - RxJs

                                     14.1 Observable

                                      14.1.1 resolved - subscribe()
                                      14.1.2 reject - catch()
                                    